          <td><font face=3D"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size=3D"2"><font =
size=3D"3"><font size=3D"2">Put simply, one British Thermal Unit [Btu] is t=
he=20
 amount of heat          required to raise the temperature of 1 pound [ lb.=
]=20
 of water 1 degree          Fahrenheit.<br>
            The Fifth International Conference on the Properties of    =20
  Steam (London, July 1956) defined the International Table calorie as =20
     4.1868 joule. <br>
   Therefore the exact conversion factor for the        International Table=
=20
 British thermal unit (Btu) is 1.05505585262 kJ.<br>
   The        thermochemical Btu is based on the thermochemical calorie whi=
ch=20
 equals        4.184 kJ exactly.</font></font><b><font size=3D"3"><br>
